# Stock firmware dump — 5.8 GB, proprietary Transsion/itel firmware. Not redistributable, too big
# for git. Keep it locally; document where to obtain it (see README / JOURNAL).
itel-RS4-S666LN-28.zip
*.stockfw.zip

# Build outputs / logs (the source tree lives at /mnt/external_nvme/aospa, not here, but guard anyway)
out/
*.log

# Editor / OS cruft
*.swp
*~
.DS_Store

# Proprietary fenrir-signed LK — not redistributed in this repo. Obtain from the device
# community (PenumbraGUI). Kept locally, gitignored.
s666ln-fenrir-signed.bin

# Proprietary 32-bit MediaTek GPU blobs (Mali GLES/Vulkan/gralloc) harvested from the stock
# firmware vendor image. Not redistributable; apply-overlays.sh step 21 documents how to
# regenerate them from itel-RS4-S666LN-28.zip. Kept locally, gitignored.
blobs32/

# Third-party OrangeFox recovery image (not ours). Obtain from the device community; patch its
# vendor_boot cmdline with patch-vendorboot-qspa.py before flashing. Kept locally, gitignored.
ofox.img

# Private release signing keys (releasekey/platform/shared/media/… .pk8 + .x509.pem). These sign
# platform-privileged code — NEVER commit or redistribute. Whoever holds them can sign an update or
# app that runs with system/platform permissions. Regenerate with development/tools/make_key if lost
# (a lost key = no more OTAs to already-flashed devices; a leaked key = compromised signing).
keys-priv/

# Personal lab journal and release announcement — kept local, not part of the public recipe.
JOURNAL.md
TELEGRAM-POST.md

# Patched proprietary MediaTek camera-HAL blobs that enable RAW/DNG (from the community
# Itel_RS4_RAW_v2 module). Not redistributable; PORT-NOTES.md "Camera RAW / DNG without root"
# documents how to obtain them. Kept locally, gitignored.
blobs-camera-raw/

# Source Magisk module the camera RAW blobs are extracted from (proprietary payload).
Itel_RS4_RAW_v2.zip

# Session handoff / next-project plan — kept local like the journal, not part of the public recipe.
RESUME-THIS.md

# USB-gadget flap logcat evidence for the v4 bug (local reference).
usb-flap-evidence.log
